
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    `gnome-terminal` yek barnamast baraye baz kardane terminal dar muhite grafiki GNOME. Ba estefade az in barnam, mitavanid dastoorat UNIX/Linux ra be soorate grafiki ejra konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--tab`     --> ➕ Yek tabe jadid baz mikonad.
    🔹 `--window`  --> 🖼  Yek panjere jadid baz mikonad.
    🔹 `-e, --command=COMMAND` --> 🚀 Dastoor ra dar terminal ejra mikonad.
    🔹 `--title=TITLE`       --> 🏷  Unvane panjere ra taeen mikonad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gnome-terminal
    
    🔹 Baz kardane yek terminal sade.

    $ gnome-terminal --tab --title="Python" -e "python3"

    🔹 Baz kardane yek tab jadid ba unvane "Python" va ejra kardane dastoor "python3".

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gnome-terminal -e "top"

    🔹 Baz kardane terminal va ejra kardane dastoor `top`. Ba in dastoor mitavanid resourse-haye CPU va memory ra dar lahze bebinid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    `gnome-terminal` is a terminal emulator for the GNOME desktop environment. It allows you to run UNIX/Linux commands in a graphical window.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--tab`     --> ➕ Opens a new tab.
    🔹 `--window`  --> 🖼  Opens a new window.
    🔹 `-e, --command=COMMAND` --> 🚀 Executes a command in the terminal.
    🔹 `--title=TITLE`       --> 🏷  Sets the window title.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gnome-terminal
    
    🔹 Opens a basic terminal window.

    $ gnome-terminal --tab --title="Python" -e "python3"

    🔹 Opens a new tab with the title "Python" and executes the "python3" command.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gnome-terminal -e "top"

    🔹 Opens a terminal and runs the `top` command. This command allows you to see real-time CPU and memory resource usage.
